    dc:description "FIGURES 1–5. Male terminalia of Oxysarcodexia. 1. Oxysarcodexia occulta Lopes (Brazil, São Paulo, Mogi Guaçu, LIE), left lateral view. 2–5. Oxysarcodexia timida (Aldrich) (Venezuela, Aragua, NHMD); phallus, showing different anatomical plans of vesica. 2. Anterolateral view (right side). 3. Posterior view. 4. Anterolateral view (left side). 5. Anterior view.Abbreviations: bp = basiphallus; C = cercus; dp = distiphallus; J = juxta; P = phallus; Po = postgonite; Pr = pregonite; Su = surstylus; V = vesica; vmb = main branch of vesica; vmp = median projection of vesica; vdl = distal lobe of vesica. Symbols: * = ventral surface of vesica; ** = dorsal surface of vesica." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4405605/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

